@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}
<h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-8">
        <p class="lead">EuroCSV is committed to protecting your privacy. This page describes how we handle your data.</p>

        <h2 class="h4 mt-4">File Handling</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Files you upload are stored in a temporary, session-specific directory on the server.</li>
            <li>Temporary files are used only to perform the requested conversion and are <strong>never shared with third parties</strong>.</li>
            <li>Temporary files are automatically purged after a maximum of 2 hours.</li>
            <li>You can initiate immediate deletion of your files at any time using the <strong>Delete My Files</strong> button on the Convert page.</li>
            <li>We do not retain any copies of your uploaded or converted files after deletion.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="h4 mt-4">Advertising</h2>
        <p>This site uses Google AdSense to display advertisements. Google may use cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits to this website or other sites.
           You may opt out of personalized advertising by visiting <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Ads Settings</a>.</p>

        <h2 class="h4 mt-4">Cookies</h2>
        <p>We use minimal cookies required for anti-forgery protection (CSRF tokens). No personal tracking cookies are set by this application.</p>

        <h2 class="h4 mt-4">Logs</h2>
        <p>Standard server access logs may be retained for security and operational purposes. These logs contain IP addresses and request metadata but do not contain the contents of your uploaded files.</p>

        <h2 class="h4 mt-4">Contact</h2>
        <p>For privacy inquiries, please open an issue on our GitHub repository.</p>
    </div>
</div>

